\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-490\li518\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin518\itap0\pararsid8206157 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Can you tell me about the house in Burns Street, what sort of house was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Oh aye, aye, it was up a stair. And - oh quite, ye ken, nice enough house then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Was it a common stair that you had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 
Well, there were - a neighbour, and were just the two like, there were a wee landing you know, and the toilet was here for - between the two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 You shared the toilet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 They shared the toilet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 How many rooms were there in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 There were three and the - kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Oh that was quite good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Oh it was a - in fact needed it for the - crowd of us you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 How about the bathroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 
Oh no, no, nothing. That's what I often the young ones and they'll say what you - I says, it used to be - the big bath. And - and down in Kirkcady street were nea bathroom, but generally you ken the big shaped tins like the zinc, but i
t's much kettle and filling up and that but it wasnae that - on Burns Street, it was just a wee washing - as we say, aye, and you got into that and - there it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Did you get a bath every week, or how often did you get one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Oh just whenever we 
took the notion or not, we never - the house was clear and that we'd - ken like, one would say I'm having tomorrow night and another one would be in it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 How about when you did have a bath, did you get a change of clothes then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Oh no - was just -
 it was just merely - getting washed down and - you ken what I mean. You ken what an ordinary - well you've never seen - ken, the baths, just a wee washing zinc bath like, a big one. But that's what you'd to get into.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 How did you get hot water for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 
Well you - there were - of course there werenae - the electric kettles or - it was a big iron kettles. And filling pots and that, that's how it was - and it was all thingymjigged in the fire. There werenae - see it was fire, an ordinary coal fire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Was it like a range?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 No, just an open fire. Aye. Uh huh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 And that's what your mother had to cook for the lot of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 And - cook on there, bake, girdles and that on the fire, and - and she'd to go through all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Was she a baker, did she make a lot of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 
Oh she's good baker. Oh aye. Of course they had all to do it in them days, you ken what I mean, because - bob's mother was the same at Noble Hill. Oh, I never - baker, wished you'd seen you woman. And there was such a f
amily of them, they were all boys, about eight - or nine boys and two lasses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 That's your mother-in-law?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Yes. And many a time we used to ken when - in the mill as I was telling Dot, if you got off just about dinnertime you'd a chance of getting 
the afternoon. But it was only once in a blue moon you see, because - if they could get a word in to you before you got out, you had to go in. But I - I used to go over to Noble Hill ken to see her like - that was during the week. No when I went down on a
 
Sunday she wasna baking then. But my if you'd seen it, she'd have her white apron on, and the plain white wooden table with white cloth, and near the girdle, and nae bother ken. She'd be talking away to you and that and there was - and all them scones. Ev
e
ry kind. And then when all they - they'd come in at teatime - and for a joke - my brother-in-law like's over there, at the top of the Avenue, many a time when I see him I - I - I - I have a laugh, and there was - oh a - dozen - more plates, with all the d
i
fferent scones. And if you'd seen them - cleared. And I'll never forget, she'd have a nice white apron and that. But she had to - she baked a lot because I mind when Bob and me were married you see, and - he says to me - oh I says, mind you Jen I'll tell 
y
ou this much, he says, I like me scone. Yes. I says, aye, and you'll get your scone all right, you ken, just in a laugh. I says, you'll get your scone, but I had to bake. I had to bake every day for him, he wouldna eat bread. But I never minded to do it, 
I never minded - doing it. And I had the - the coal fire just with the big girdle, I don't ken where my girdle went. It was in the house for years but I don't know where it went. And I had to bake - with the girdle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 How did your mother do, did she have an oven at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 
She - she just had this wee oven in the fireplace. And if she's got - and - but a wee fire, ken, down here. I can, I can picture it like and a - a wee fire and it was just a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7291225\charrsid9768143 wea}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 ken, oven like this. Just a wee thing. And that's where she did her - baking tarts or - cakes or wot in that, that's where it was in.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Did she ever make jam and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Oh ah, oh she was - oh ah, she was one to - of course it was the cheapest and that - I mean it was cheap then, I'm not saying nowada
ys making jam, I don't know whether - but oh you ken it was cheaper then and that but she had to bake - make her own jam. I mind we used to go for the jar covers you ken and - we - cello or whatever it is, fitting them on and we used to - stick the - the 
- covers on for her and write ken what - gooseberry or strawberry or owt like that, but oh the fruit it was cheap then. But she'd a big braw stewing pot. And that's what it was made in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 All made on the fire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 On the fire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 How about the washing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Well - just -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Was there a wash house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Were no wash house, just the big pot for washing in too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Done in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 In the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 How about drying, did you have a back green to dry them on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 And - well, there were
 - there were a big wooden partition ken up along here, like - for the other side of the - ken the houses like you know. And I mind my father-in-law, that's what he did really dear, he went and he put pulleys, and the rope and my mother just turned the ro
p
e ken like that, and - the clothes went along. That place then it was not - or she wouldnae go in, but - when the steam - at - Burns Street, it opened, there were a place, they called it the Mulhoe then, it opened for ken going with your washing like what
 
they do - the launderette or something now. Well it was just you ken and paid so much an hour for to do, and old Jessie used to be doing it, and you got them dried too, you ken, pay so much and just in a drier. And that was handier yes, for her and that, 
but it was a big - iron pot, and I can mind three legs, and there it used to go in that fire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 How about your clothes, did your mother make any of your clothes or were they all bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Well to tell you the truth I think they were just all handed d
own. That's what it were - ken like, although I never - I - I - I just - wasnae very guilty and I didnae - although you ken and that in them days I was more temporary, I didna fancy ken and that, but our Jessie, my oldest sister and that, and she would - 
wear - jumble sale - clothes and get them shortened or - oh Jessie would have had - 'cos Jenny - always known for that. Oh just didna care about their skin, wearing other folks clothes, or even our Jessie's. I was the only one like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 With a big family like that they would have to be handed down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 
Aye. And - well, and they the likes - mother's sisters had they been the same, well - it would just have been a case of it you ken. But I'll say that much even we ken for your - for yourself like, I'm
 not talking about the young ones now, but - I mean even they'll talk about their short skirts and things and that. Oh I can mind - I never wore long clothes. I didna wear long clothes then, and I could mind when the hobbles - come into go. And I used to 
