 away Georgetown, I used to walk there, this Miss Kane was a tailoress, and I used to go away - out there to get my clothes made. And this wee costume. And - of course Miss Kane says, what do you ken? Oh well, I says, I want a hobble. And it was only you 
k
en what they - what they call them - whether the mini is or no now they call them I don't know, but you just strided in them. I've - I've skirts in there and that and that's the - I don't in case I fall like that so I have to wear this one for - for - but
 hob - we called them hobbles.
