l, it was cheaper and that right enough. But - ken he just come to that stage day, he wouldna do owt like that, he wouldna be bothered.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Did you always get new shoes or were they handed down sometimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Well no, never - I never mind - I never - o
h no, I - I - I never mind wearing ken - handed down shoes or owt because I mean even for your feet and that - just the same as them, I've had them for years and still as I say - they've come in handy because they're that comfortable on my feet, and that 
t
hat - that's what I said to the doctor, and I called - I call them my hunting shoes. But I put them on but I put the slippers on for a wee change, but oh no, the - ken what I mean even - shoes or owt like that or even what we called sand shoes, what - at 
the school used to say gym shoes. Well all - just called them sand shoes, you got them for sixpence a pair, depending on your size.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 But you never had to go without shoes then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Oh no, no. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7291225\charrsid9768143 No, barring if the sun was shin}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 ing and taking your shoes off to run -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 If you wanted to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Did your father help much in the house at all, even in the earlier days? Would he do much to help your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Oh I - I - I don't - think - I mind her always saying like about - the first 10 year of h
er married life - was - ken - happy. But he used to get out and get a drink. No drunk like I mean. That - that's the way she put it once to me, ken, when I started once, ken, when I was - saying one day and says - Help me, I don't know what kind of man he
 
is. I says, oh he - he would - oh really, and you ken poor soul, that's what she turned round and said. Well she said, the first ten year of my married life was happy. And then he stopped the drink. Went off this. Wouldn't - wouldn't spend a ha'penny. He 
wouldn't spend a ha'penny. It was all him saving.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Do you think he would help with decorating the house and doing that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Oh, no, I don't think he - didna think he did anything like that and - my oldest sister like and that, was when s
he got an age she was paperer. Ken, she was a great one. Even she'd have done it if you'd said to her, come on - she loved papering. She used to do all mine and that, she - never was asked either, she just, you ken, even when Bob was ill and that and she 
w
ould say, oh well, she said, I'll do it, and ken I used to say, oh I'll try and do it myself Jess. But - you ken, you're not trying it, I - I'll do it. But she loved paper - she was a great one for decorating. But I canna say that I can mind my father, I 
canna mind.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Did he ever take much to do with you children when you were small? Would he ever take you out without your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Dinna think he took us out at all. It was just a case of - go - his work. Getting his tea, ye ken, cleaning himself, w
ashing himself, I'm no going to say dressing himself, and away a walk, back again, got his supper, into bed. Up and out at six in the morning again just like what we were. And the same thing, that's what went on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 He never helped with the wee ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Never, oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Bathing them or dressing them and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 
He never - no - that - that's what I really say, I don't understand ken men and that who - ken like - oh well, Bob wasna like ken, I mean wouldn't have said he was a Jessie o
r owt - owt and that but - ye ken, help ye. And I could have telled him anything. And got his advice, but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Did you have any jobs to do in the house when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Oh we had our work to on Friday night and - well - oh well, maybe running a
ll - use to be the message hand and Jessie was one, she was the nurse, ken, nursing weans or taking them out, you ken, the - the younger ones I mean. But I was the message - lassie, I run all the messages. But on a Friday night, we'd all our own bit, like
 
all had to do this room and our Jess another you know, and Lily the other one, but we had to do that afore - even if we were going out we had to do our room before we gout out. But then werena ken, say at a dance or owt like that. Oh no, you'd to be in at
 
a certain time. Ten o'clock through the week. Nine on a Sunday night. That - I mean you didna get, ken, I - I could enjoy myself when I was out like that that, but it was just a case of - you had to be in because the fear was on you, he always made - you 
k
now, he - ken - you'd get locked out, you'll get - well that always used to fear good, and I can mind one Sunday night, sitting at the top of the Craigs, that was and I's - favourite walk, and we used to sit there, oh it was lovely, ken, and - he would be
 
telling me this place and all you ken, and where they were and that, and I can mind this Sunday night and I happened to say, what's the time Bob? And of course it was a packet watch, I have it - I it's in the drawer yet, and he - just going on to nine o'c
lock. Oh and I just got up. Oh, I said, and I can mind we run from the top of the Craigs to that house in Burn's Street. And we hadna time even you ken - no - no time to say goodnight and up them stairs and got into the house.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Did you make it in time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 
I got in anyway. I got in, aye, I can mind of that, that's what I often say - you ken, I'll say to Nessie - now young ones and that, heavens they're only - some of them's only going out at ten o'clock at night. And I says your old mother had to be i
n. In at nine, a Sabbath night you had to be in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Did your younger brothers and sisters have to do any jobs in the house, or was it just the older ones that got it to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Oh just the old - just - the same with every family, it was the older ones 
that got it. The younger ones got, ken, that was - time was going on, the wee bit things better than one thing and another and then getting married and then they were away out, but the old fellow you know what I mean - he was left up there, on his own. Li
ke they all got married, he was left up there. And then we - we - Johnnie and Bessie, ken, running about and so forth, that's how. But I never bothered, no, I never - I cannae - I mean it's an awful thing to say but no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 You just didn't get on with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 You say you had to be in at a certain time, were you expected to go to your bed at a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Oh well of course at the school we were away bedded early because I mean he was - himself. Nine o'clock. And you had to be, you ken.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 How old would you be when you started to put yourself to bed? Would you be quite young do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 
Oh I think we would be all young I think, it was a case of just all helping each other and all but - oh I think and that - oh just - aye, yes, for to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Did you have to sleep with somebody when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 
I sleep - them days as I tell our ones, they'd not believe it, there were maybe two at - the top of the bed and two at the bottom. And there were two small rooms and there were a 
big room and there were beds in it. And of course - my father never slept, you ken, my ma was left in the kitchen. And it was iron beds. He never slept with my ma, not that I can mind of. He got away into the room and he had to have that bed by himself, k
en, a single bed. He had to, and then my brothers, there would be - maybe about four of them in that bed. And then there were the four of us in this other bed, as well, and it was top and bottom.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Did you always slept the same way, did you and your sister always sleep in the same bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Oh aye, the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Or did you swap round, did you change the place you were sleeping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Oh no, just you ken, the two of us at the top. And then - likes of well, our Lily and me, we liked at the top of the bed, an
d Jessie and Maisie, well they rather - they had to take the bottom like or not. And the boys were the same, I mean the - the families and that they were alike. They were the same then. Maybe that's the reason why I cannae sleep myself, I don't know. But 
I you were younger then and that that - you just didnae think about it ken. Been different ken, sleeping with brothers or owt like that, they wouldn't have liked, ken, the likes of that. Oh no, there were none of that, no, there were none of that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Not even when you were quite small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Oh no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 How about eating, where did you eat, in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Just in the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 You must have needed a big table if you were all going to sit down at once?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Aye, I'm telling - a big - oh yes,
 I mind Bob - made me once - it - it went out too I think. Just a big kitchen plain table ken, white wood plain, but Bob and that and - and the four legs and that, that's - ken maybe - when we were married first like and he just, you ken, he wasnae - hadn
ae the - doings then, and - and the four legs I mind he - he had a wee - machine and kind of thingummyjigged them, and I had that table for years, and that's where I baked and everything on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Did you ever eat in any of the other rooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Not for special occasions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 No. No, we'd all - just in - everything ken was in - done in the kitchen. Your sink and everything was in there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Can you tell me about breakfast? Your father would be up first and have his breakfast before you were up?
