Oh well the boys - they were mostly at their practice, you kwn at the Town Hall like that was in Shakespeare Street. They were mostly at the Hall practicing you ken, always at - something on there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 They didn't practice at home much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 
Oh - oh they did their time for that you ken, I've seen them going into the room having a blow like and that and so forth. As I tell you, that brother up the Lockerbie Road, he was - onl
y nine - and he gave his first solo in the - Drill Hall, and ken when I see - there's that wee boy in there singing and carrying on and then it struke me one afternoon I says, Mercy me, no need to talk. My own brother was only nine, oh I didna mind it, bu
t I says, he was only nine when he first solo in the Drill Hall. And he must have been away - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Did your parents ever play any games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Oh no. I tell you and that my father and that it was just his work and away out for a walk. Back, get
 his supper and into bed. Up the next day, just the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 And your mother would be busy looking after you all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 My mother - that's - she had plenty you ken what I mean. And if no she - ken she used to take us up to my granny's, that was in the Hi
gh Street like, we hadnae far ken, as I talk about that Mill Hole for the Burns's House and cut through, and - just up the High Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Sometimes you played games maybe of a night like snakes and ladders or ludo or something like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 She would never sit and play that kind of thing with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 
Oh - I've seen, you ken, me, I mind I bought a - a ludo and it was only sixpence. I'd to say up for it like and that but I got a ludo and it was only sixpence, and many a time we used to sit 
and play ken. At that. And my ma - I - I - it was of course me, I used to say, come on ma and have a shot you ken and see ken and that and just - of course my father was away out and that, and we got away with - I'm no saying we got away with some - but y
o
u ken we were more freer when he wasnae in, and you could enjoy yourself and have a laugh where - if he'd been in it would have been a case of coming out and saying, what's going on, what's going on, and that dumped you, that was the finish and that. Spoi
led the whole thing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 
Can you remember anything that you did with your mother and father at Christmas time when you were wee? What was Christmas like when you were wee? You would hang your stockings up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 We hung our stockings up but - all that we 
got was an orange and an apple and two or three sweeties. And then I was very old, I tell you, it was a wee sweetie shop and maybe it would be no more than sixpence, we - we ken bought a - ken, just a wee thing, and I can mind that Christmas - Oh I was ov
er the moon with that wee shop. I think everybody - ken the lassies like even at the school - oh I thought it was great you ken, and it would cost no more than sixpence I don't suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 How old would you be then do you think? Obviously you were at the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 
Oh aye, it was after I was - oh aye. I'd be at the school for a while before you ken - I got the likes of that. We certainly hung our stocking because I can always mind ken the fireplace, and we all had you ken, in fact we used to - I used to
 write my name on my stocking as if, you ken, of course there were no - well ken, not today, all - we knitted them at the school, our own ken but there it was and that. And I used to have mine, I made sure you ken, but that's - that's all we got.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Did you have any special meals at Christmas, like now you get a big Christmas dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Oh no, no. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Would you have a Christmas cake or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 No. Never had anything like that either. That's what Nessie'll say to me too, she'll say, I di
nna ken - in fact to tell you the truth, it's - it was for Linda like that I - I used to get - get a wee tree, I liked - decorating it then, and then - it finished up an artificial one. And oh I used to ken - because Linda was - when she was young, and sh
e
 ken, she likes anything like that, just like any other wean, and I used to sit many an hour decorating it, that I've all the - ken, the decorations like, all in bags, and I used to spend - oh and I was in my glory. And of course - now - you see I've got 
a
way from that too. And of the one at home of course, Irene, oh she'll bring it, we have it in a big bag you ken, the tree, and she brings it out and of course decorates it up and it's only you ken for the - for the likes of her, 'cos Linda - Linda's like 
that too, like any other she thinks there ought to be ken a tree. She wouldna say to you like and that, but still I know and - I mean I'm no out of pocket because I've had it for years.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Did many folks have Christmas trees when you were wee, can you remember seeing any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 
Oh no. No, I canna. But maybe at the - Sunday school ken, our - Christmas - do like, a wee tree maybe you ken like and getting a wee present maybe, no much and that, but getting the likes of that, but it was only at the Sunday school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 How about birthdays, did you get anything for your birthday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 I canna mind ever getting anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 You don't remember any of your wee brothers or sisters having a birthday or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 I cannae mind - well, maybe the youngest one, I
 think our Walter, he would maybe get a wee thing you ken, but there's an awful thingummyjig between us, and that but I still say even at the present I think the younger ones ken get - are inclined to get a wee bit more and that but - I think our Walter w
as the only - only one - that ever got a wee thing. That's the one, he was born - when the Titanic - was - sunk. That Sunday night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 How about Newspapers, did your mother and father get any newspapers regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Well - that - Weekly News as he cal
led it like, we used to call it, the Dundee News you ken. My ma used to get it. And on a Sunday - now what was that paper? She used to get a Sunday paper. The News of the World. But - Irene always ken - I'm always saying about getting - I says, I think I'
l
l have a change to the Sunday Mail. I think I'll - get the - the News of the World. Oh she says, get away, she says, you're no getting yon paper with all the scandal, all this, ken, she just - gets it off her chest. But anyway I says - oh well, I says - i
t's just for a bit of a change. But - my father of course, it was his paper. And my ma had to - and the - Bulletin. Ken. A daily - the Bulletin. That's what was in our house. But my ma got them like and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Did you bairns get a chance to read them or did you not bother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 
Oh I used to like reading the paper. I, ken, even yet that I like ken if I read a paper and kind of tally things up and that it's just the same as shops and anything, and the prices and that. I sit and I - I study like them up. O
h just to - ken - or maybe - maybe - having more time I don't know and that but still I know and it just - I mean keeps me going.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Was your father a reader then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Oh he liked his paper. And I mean it was always maybe - after his tea he'd have a s
kip through, and then away out for - ken, just down to the Suspension - there used to be a week - dyke do you ken, off the Brig, and the tuners ken, and the - men from the mill, there, and then away they went a walk. And back again, by the time he'd come 
i
n it was supper time. And maybe a wee - and then, off to bed. And you werenae long till you had to - vamoose too. Of course there were nae - no wireless or anything like that, you had to - as I tell you that wee gramophone. Three and six. And when I think
 
of them records, you - I dinna ken - if they're - on the go. I can - mind ken of what I - and slip them on like the - like the barrel like just slip it on. Just - and old fashioned, that's how you ken - this woman through the wall, she had - well, his wif
e died like and that and then he married her just - about six month after, I was only down here - a week and that when - his wife died - it used to be terrible, that's years ago.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Was there much difference of opinion between Catholics and Protestants here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Oh - oh then, oh aye, they - they - and the Catholics like and that, the likes of Glasgow, that's where you seen the parades.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 What about down here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 And - well there werenae so much - you ken, down here like and that. There were just th
at wee - ken, and that, no that it made any difference to me, because the simple reason - I run mates with a lassie - and she was a Catholic.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Did she go to a different school from you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Aye, oh she went to a Catholic school in Brooke Street like 
and I went to St Michael Street. But still - Maggie and I got on like that. And then - here, on a Sunday, like I'd go to my own Sunday school like, and then after - after - getting your dinner like and that and you - you went out ken afternoon. We used to
 
- land away to the Convent. I used to go with Maggie to the Convent. And of course - I can mind it was like a big veil, and all the - you ken, the folk - we just heard kind of voices like, but - you were sitting facing this way ken like an altar, and they
 
seemed to be at the back of you, but you couldnae, ken pick them out but oh the lovely voices. And then it was then - it - and - you ken, it didna - it didna say inside but I said to Maggie like anyway, I says, where was yon voices coming? You'd have actu
a
lly thought it - it was coming from the heavens, you ken? Oh lovely sweet voices. So Maggie telled me. Oh, she says, Jennie, she says, that was the nuns. She says, you couldnae - but they were at back of you like. Got a big heavy kind of veil or something
, and she says, it was them. Oh, I says, what lovely singing, oh really and honestly, you ken, it was. Anyway, we used to - then on a Sunday night - we finished up at the chapel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 What did your mother and father think about this then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 At wait now
. I think about him. Here Maggies says - to me this Sunday now, she says - we'll go to the - she didna say chapel, she said, we'll go to the church like. She says, what about coming Jennie? Oh, no harm in it. I says, aye, I will, I says, I'll come. So of 
c
ourse she warned me. She says, there's only one thing. She says, you ken, you'll have to - ken, kneel, do this. I had to put my hand in the water, the Holy Water, and - I had to cross myself. And she says - ken, will you do it, because - ken there were pr
i
ests and father or something around it, but anyway she says - you ken. I says, certainly. Well I thought well - I thought nothing about it. I says, certainly. And of course when we come - went into the door and this - big thing whatever it is in the bowl 
w
ith the Holy Water, oh heavens I put my hand in and all the water was over, ken I was that excited, and Maggie looking as much as you ken. But anyway - then when she come to - ken, where we were going to sit - we had to get down and, you ken, like this, a
n
d we got in. Well, I went to chapel with Maggie for long enough. To here - my father got to hear about it, and oh he's bitter against the Catholics. Would you believe that? Oh, what a bitter man, ken, with the Catholics. But anyway, here of course it was,
 
oh - oh for long enough and I fair enjoyed it, went to the convent as I telled you - in the afternoon, finished off in the chapel. But I was at my own Sunday school, it was at two o'clock like in Irish Street, Greyfriars. Always was at my Sunday school li
k
e. And if there was anything special on at the church like, but I was always at the convent, and I - I - I liked the - the nuns singing, it was lovely, and going to the chapel at night. So here this - it was a Monday dinnertime as usual. Sitting at the si
d
e of him like and he says, where was you last night Jennet? Oh of course never thinking - I telled him. I telled him the truth like. He says, yes, he says, I heard all about it. This had been - a weaver - was good enough to tell him. Oh maybe the woman of
 
course never meant nothing by it, just like ourselves maybe passing ken, oh I seen your daughter at the chapel, or anything, maybe no, but he mae it such - so he says - oh it's - true enough? Aye, I says, I went with Maggie and that, I says, I go to the c
o
nvent in the afternoon. And I says, I've done it for a long time. Well, he says, you go - keep away from them two places. Now, he says, if I hear - about you being back - and that finished it. Now would you believe that? And still I got pleasure out of - 
ken - I - I went with Maggie and - and I - I really thoroughly enjoyed it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 You said your father was in the Masons? They're very much anti-Catholic aren't they? You didn't get Catholics in the Masons I don't think.

