\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Would you take food with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 
Aye, aye, our mothers you ken, had - ken, so much, but it wouldna be much in those and that, maybe sandwiches and - a loaf like that, but the boys, they used to go down with an earlier bus and like my brothers and the
m other ones, they used to go in - and in the wood and make a wee fire and boil a kettle for to make tea for - for us arriving and then we just - then enjoyed ourselves, we just run wild you ken and that. Thoroughly enjoyed it but - that's all the - the o
utings I can - ken really mind when we were younger like. Bar as I say the Sunday school - trip too. We always, once - like yearly, we always went the Sunday school trip.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 We as that to Glencaple too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Oh no. No, no. The likes of that - Duncan as I
 was talking about - the Tories they called them, I think it was the same ones and that, used to - go to you ken his ground like, like a big house and that, Newlands, and, ken, round about his ground, and, ken, kind of special ones like that and - invitin
g
 you you ken, and you got there - got the - maybe a wee bit field and that, and that's really how we spent - oh no, they took - oh no to Glencaple, didna go to Old Quay or anything like that but - oh no, I'll give them their due there. But it was the wago
nnettes just the same and then of course buses come - on the go after that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Did you run races and have games and things at your trip?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Oh aye, running races and that and ken you always got - a wee prize, you kwn, if you won like and that. But - it
 was really - and that - was worth it and then, of course, we'd nothing to take like, they had the big hamper ken with - what you wanted. But they were catering for you, you just had to take it or leave it like and that but - like they had it - like this 
big hamper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 
Was there much difference in the way you spent Saturdays when you were at the school? Before you started working in Wyllies and doing the wee jobs?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 No, if I could - every day was just the same, bar the - like maybe - going to the mat
inee. And that was the - the Electric - the Electric Theatre, like pictures, the likes of them daft ones on there that I've seen some of their old faces, you ken, on there. But it was just a - like - if - if you went on a Saturday afternoon, as you called
 the matinee, I - even - I've heard the weans talk about the minors now, maybe something like that, it only cost - a penny - to get in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 So you went quite often did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Aye - oh aye, oh - ken, just to spend the time and that. But there were crowd
s of us as Ken often says, likes of - them alssies even living in the street - aside of me and that and I run about - there were quite a crowd of us and we thoroughly enjoyed it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 What about Sunday then, did you get dressed up on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Oh aye. Dressed up for the occasion.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 You would go to the church in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 
And - well, no - ken when - oh after I started - like when I joined the church - then I, ken, I had to - attend it like. But was younger than that it was the Sunday school,
 and of course - we used to ken - up the stair in the hall and of course, young ones and then you were up there for a year and that and then when you came down the stair, just like the - the school, coming to the primary into the - and there's all we clas
ses and, ken, young ones. Learning, getting taught and that - and the subject and that and so forth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 
