Which. Yes. I - I've - oh I - I listen and all them wee - wee things you ken, I take note of, like and that. And - I said to Nessie, I says, even, I says, I canna understand. I says, one minister - one minister, who art, 
but then I've heard other ones, which art, which we were - taught.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 It might depend on the church that they're from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Oh well - aye, maybe - I don't know, I have the - the - the Bible ken and it's - oh my ma gave it to me for my birthday or someth
ing once, I - I've had it for years like and the Lord's Prayers in the back of it - and it's, which are in Heaven. And I got into that, and I've seen me, ken, when I'm in my bed like, I canna get down on my knees, but when I'm in my bed like and that and 
I've seen me ken say, which, and then I, ken, oh art, who art, you ken, this the way I'm going on in bed, before I fall asleep.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 You say your mother went out quite a bit then if she was visiting your granny and she went to the Salvation Army?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Well that's the only recreation she had and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Was she quite friendly with the other women in the street then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Oh yes. Oh that's what I say, I mean in them days and all, they were just all like one big family I've telled you. It was just a case o
f - your mother would help my mother or - or have you got - are you going up the Street Mrs Mellor? Will you bring me so and so? Are you Mrs Morley, bring me so and so. And it was harmony, it was, you ken what I mean. I canna describe what it was like, be
cause it was just all - and the families were all the same. No fighting, nae nothing, that's funny, there were nae fighting, no even the boys and that, were nae fighting nor no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 It doesn't seem natural to have boys and no fights?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Aye, well I - an
d I'm telling you the boys and us, oh we used to play a lot together. And there were never, ken, a word out of place. And when I think too and that, we used to get away down to the Kinnel - and we'd join in with the boys, football. Ken, just kicking the b
a
ll, but the boys used to you ken to say, that's good, go on, you're doing well. And - and still - we enjoyed every minute of that. Because we had nae - nae money. But then as I say, I mean - we were all the same like and that. I quite admit and that that 
-
 we maybe kenned nae different, I don't know, I - I - I don't know, maybe you ken just brought up that way of - of living just the same as young ones now, well, they're - you cannae expect you ken on young shoulders and that - and - ken, going away back t
hen. But I mean, I've - happy memories of - every minute. For all what, you ken, I mean, but then I was brought, ken like the rest, we were brought up - we thought nothing about it. For enjoyment we'd to make our own.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 It surprised me that you never fell out with any of your pals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 
