\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Aye, well - there were only - well Rachel you ken what I 
mean, her father had that business, and then there were - this - Molly Morrison. I never heard - that - I never heard that lassie's name mentioned, but they lived in a house in Broom's Road, but it was - their own house then, and that's going back a bit. 
Her father was a cattle dealer, just like Johston the cattle and that, her father was a cattle dealer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 So they would have more money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 And - but - on the whole, Molly and that, that was another one, and we got on that well with her ken, but - I've
 often said to our young ones today, too, that's the only - I said, there's such controls and that now, but we used to go through to the sixth standard, finished off at the ex-sixth, and then off to George Street we went, like, they that passed like and t
h
at. But Molly and that, oh really, and oh just an ordinary, ken, nice lassie, didnae - act it nor nothing, and that lassie I must say, oh she was clever. And every year - every standard we went into - Molly, the McLel - we called it the McLellan prize, of
 course she was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13396319\charrsid9768143 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 
ix with the school at the finish, but the McLellan prize. And she'd a chain, and it was a half crown and a book to go with it. And every prize giving Molly had this chain. And then there were a hole - she got a hole made ken in a half crown
 and it was put onto that chain. And she was a lassie and that - no swell headed nor nothing like that. An extra nice lassie, ken what I mean. She wasnae swelled headed or - or tipped herself any way. And I mean, that's only one I could say, ken, all the 
rest of us and that - that were - our fathers worked in the mills and things like that, but still and on - I mean Molly and that and - she was - different but didnae - were nae difference.
