Oh well - ken, I mean, I'll say you ken, there was some - it wasnae that I'm no saying there werena smart or - or they couldnae do it, but they just didnae seem to - I think bother
 themselves. And still and on even strapping, I'll give my father his due, that was one thing, ken it was a case of - ken - not hitting, ken when we were wee. Dinna start hitting. If they canna take a telling, when spoken to, dinna start - you weren't to 
-
 and I was the same with my own three. I never lifted my hand even - even yet do it. Because as I say and that, well it's right enough, if they cann just - ken what I mean, well it was different I mean I'm no saying now with a young family bringing them u
p on my own, I don't think could do it, but I mean, Bob was like that too, you ken what I mean. They just didna get away with a thing. And he wasnae like hard on them or anything like that, but it was for their own food.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 You were saying that your father had this strap?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 
And that - my father with them tawse, and I'm telling you he used to put them in the fire to hard - harden them. It would be sorer on you. And still - he never - because he didna - he - he didna even believe, he says, aye well, bel
ting - doesna do so because you can knock weans just - and that's how I never ken - at the school and that. But I mean when - old Beaky Henry as we called him like and that, like we just went on from one standard to another, my God it learnt me. If he did
 ask me, I used to - I used to shout out and that, I says to myself, never again - and if I'd ever have got the strap from him again I - I don't know what I would have done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Make sure you speak into the right ear?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 And, aye, believe me and I under
stand the man because - I often think and that too, ken, I often think if somebody would get my ears, I - I feel, ken, it's the wax. And folk'll say, oh get them syringed, and - of course Irene once she got hers did, but she says never again, she says, yo
u
'd be daft, because she says, my God, I wouldna suffer you again, but I feel you ken, and I just say to myself - well ken, going away back in them - poor old soul, ken, a wee bit deaf and that. And it's - I can under - yes, folk would have nae time and th
at for that but - still and on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Were the hours that you went to the High School the same as the ones at St Michaels? Ir did you have to stay longer at the school then?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Oh no, just - nine in - and - finished at four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 How about your dinner, did you manage to get home for your dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Oh yes. Oh aye, we always struggled for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 You would have quite a run home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Oh it werenae far - that far you ken, from George Street down to - Burns's Street you ken what I mean, it was just down 
the High Street you ken and that. But I always went home because as I say and that, our ken our mother's and that in them days, was a big pot of soup, and - the cheapest like, the big pot of soup, well - but - never - dinners and that, I didnae - I never 
-
 I cannae mind ever any of them stopping for their dinner. Of course they didna come from - away up the country and that as they do now. I mean the likes of - the - is here anyway and that, they come with even buses and that, but there were none of that, 
it was more ken just the town hands.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Did you like the school then or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Oh - oh I - I - oh I liked the school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Do you have any regrets maybe that you didn't stay at school longer, anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Ah well, as I say and that, I me
an, we never even got the - no like now, they have your leaving age, and they say you leave at fifteen, now it's got to be - it's sixteen. Well when you were fourteen, you left, it didnae matter when it was. No before holidays or anything, whenever you co
m
e fourteen - you left on your birthday. And the likes of me, well, I wasnae so bad, with running messages for them three shops but with Wyllie the baker, well I had that job right away, that I could just leave, although it was only two and six a week mind
. That was my pay. And that was all day, from seven 'til you time at night, and that two and six was my pay. But there were only one and that and it was - that Molly Morrison as I tell you, Molly went to the Academy. She was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10710664\charrsid9768143 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 ix like that but she went to th
e Academy, Milly didna go to the High School. But she was rally, ken, clever like and that. But there were nae - I think - they mostly all ken like, they just left the school, I mean it wasnae a case of, if you've nae - work or that you'll just carry on. 
You just left and that was - the whole thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 What about night classes? Was there anything like that in your day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Well that's - I - some had to - had to attend night classes like and that. But there were two or three of us and that, and it was mo
stly to pass our time in. We used to go to the night class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 What did you go for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 
And it was just the usual - like what we did at the school. Cooking and things like that. And likely took a lesson, like some like - clerical work like and that for
 - them smart ones like, taking - some - that were - some that went into offices like, that's what they took, but we didna, you ken, the crowd of us and that used to go and it helped to pass the night in. And then our - teacher and that, like Miss Crichto
n, she was there at night. Yes, aye, just maybe two nights a week like and that then. And it was - it was grand, you ken, helped to pass the time in.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 How did you get your first job with Wyllies? Did they just ask you if you wanted a job, or did you go and offer, or how did it come about?

