Well as I - as - as I said to you and that, my granny used to - she washed dishes for Wyllie the baker as I tell you, like pies - catered like, pies and peas, tripe suppers and catering for drives and things like
 that, and my granny - used to wash dishes because you ken what I mean for they piled up and the two - like Jenny Wyllie and Annie like the daughters, they were in the shop. And here it just so happened - Mrs Wyllie - asked my granny, and if she thought k
e
n I would go, and give a wee help. So - of course - there I got started there and it was just a case, you ken what I mean, it was - well you done this wee thing, you did the next thing, you thought nothing about it like, but - of course they wouldnae do i
t
 nowadays but - I mean you did this wee - and you did the next wee thing, and then it come to what about, you ken, coming - to work. And that was delivering rolls seven o'clock down that Middle Road and that, that - Mullen - Muller, he was a German bus sh
e
 was an Englishwoman but my God, oh she was terrible. If I wasnae down there at seven in the morning to deliver them rolls I didna half get tarter and that, and then - just - like - there are like two villas like and - the Muller's door facing this and th
i
s - boss of the McGeorge's - factory, him that manages, Johnny - Marshall as I - I talked about and that, that was another old friend of my fathers like they were all - and of course it was - it was him that put it into my head and that - about the factor
y
. In fact he asked me, he says, what does - Wyllie - oh this is ken when I'd left the school - no cheeky Jenny, what does - what does he - of course you ken they knew each other well and that because they used to visit you ken in Brooke Street or down Mil
l
 - how much - no cheeky, how much does he - you ken, and of course I never thought, I says - half a crown. Would you no like to come into the factory? I'm sure your mother could do with ken an extra shilling or two. You'd make more in the factory. Oh I ju
s
t - as I went away back to this shop and that I said - I telled them that, I says, oh, I'll think it over. And I'm going along St Micheal's Street, I says - him well, if I could you ken, I'd be better in there. So here - I didna - I waited and that and th
e
n I says - I said to my ma like and that I says - ken - Johnny Marshall was - saying to me about, ken, the factory. What do you think - are you no ken content where you are? I thought she was going to say, oh, ken, ask your father, of course it was, in th
e
m days, even - that it was silly enough you ken, ask your father. Well anyway - here - I says to my mother, I've made my mind up. I said, I'll tell Johnny in the morning. You ken, and - I'm going into the factory. And it was pulling gloves. Of course from
 that I used to learn finger, maybe, you ken someone with a frame and I would say, have a wee shot at it, you ken, and I was picking it up all the time. With gloves like. I was picking it up all the time.
