 no. No, no. That's where I got my training, maybe I would go to this one, and I would say, could I have a wee shot at your frame. And that was finger - in fact the hand machine too, and then fingering. Oh no, didnae get - no, no. They didna - like they t
o
ok them from the school now, I rene says the other week there were a crowd of them, all down you ken, young ones going through the factory. Oh no, there were none of that, it was just a case of - I picked it up myself because - I wanted to learn, right en
o
ugh, but anyway - I just got kind of settled at the job - when he went away and he - he, got a job, weaving in the mill says to me. My father says to me sitting and that, he says - go in the mill and you'll make more money. Of course his word was lawa and
 
that. Silly me, you ken like, I says - oh dear me, after ken Johnny Marshall being as good and - I telled him that - that - when he got me in it and that so - anyway, I just telled the man the honest truth. I says, it's my father, I says, I says, you get 
o
n with him like he wants me at the mill, I says, and, I says, I'm quite content where I am but, I says, I've to go to the mill, I says. And of course Johnny kenned what he was - and that, but anyway, I went into the mill as I tell you and that. My heart w
as never in that place. I never - it wouldnae appeal to me at all that.
