\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 How about your father, how do you think he felt about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 Well - to tell you the truth and that - his history, cannae - I couldna say even ken that much about him. Because, I mean, it was just 
- had his own way of living. But he was a man - he'd no time for neighbours. He'd hardly pass the time of day. Because I can mind a - a Mrs - Murphy saying to my ma once and that she says, oh, she says, I dinna ken she says, your man, she says - ken he'll
 
no pass the time of day. And my ma was awfully - but, no - he never - seemed with neighbours, ken like, say - your man would go out and have a - if your neighbour or anybody standing, well, would say, oh good morning or something you ken what I mean. Aye 
well, no, he never - bothered much - that was one thing - he never bothered with neighbours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8206157 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 How about the folk where he worked, you said he went out with some of the other loom tuners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1604703 JR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid921314\charrsid9768143 The men. Yes. Just - just a certain clique now.
